# Count-Min Sketch: approximate frequency counting
direction: down

Title: "COUNT-MIN SKETCH: 'how many times did item X appear in the stream?'" {
  style: { fill: "#fff4c2"; stroke: "#bf360c"; stroke-width: 2; border-radius: 10 }
}

Structure: "STRUCTURE: a 2D array of counters: d rows \u00d7 w columns\n  d = number of hash functions (rows)\n  w = number of counters per row\n  Each row has its own independent hash function" {
  style: { fill: "#bbdefb"; stroke: "#0d47a1"; stroke-width: 2; border-radius: 10 }
}

Update: "UPDATE(x, count):\n  for each row i in 1..d:\n    j = hash_i(x) mod w\n    counters[i][j] += count\n\n  (item x lands at one cell per row, hashed independently)" {
  style: { fill: "#c8e6c9"; stroke: "#1b5e20"; border-radius: 8 }
}

Query: "QUERY(x): estimate the count of x\n  for each row i in 1..d:\n    j = hash_i(x) mod w\n    candidates.append(counters[i][j])\n  return MIN(candidates)        # MIN reduces overestimate\n\n  The MIN works because collisions only ADD to counts;\n  the smallest of d candidate counters has the fewest collisions." {
  style: { fill: "#fff59d"; stroke: "#bf360c"; border-radius: 8 }
}

Properties: "PROPERTIES:\n  \u2022 NEVER UNDERESTIMATES (some collisions inflate counts)\n  \u2022 Error bound: with w=O(1/\u03b5) and d=O(log 1/\u03b4),\n    overestimate \u2264 \u03b5 \u00d7 total_stream_count with probability 1-\u03b4\n  \u2022 Heavy hitters: keep a top-K list updated alongside sketch\n  \u2022 Mergeable: add cell-wise across sketches \u2192 distributed counting" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: { fill: "#e1bee7"; stroke: "#4a148c"; border-radius: 8 }
}

Use: "REAL-WORLD USES:\n  \u2022 streaming TOP-K (most-frequent IPs, URLs, words)\n  \u2022 DDoS detection: 'which IPs have made > 10k requests this minute?'\n  \u2022 network monitoring: heavy-flow detection in routers\n  \u2022 NLP: frequency tables in fixed memory (word2vec preprocessing)\n  \u2022 Twitter: trending-topic detection alongside HLL for unique users\n  \u2022 Cassandra: internal sketch for compaction decisions" {
  shape: rectangle
  style: { fill: "#ffe0b2"; stroke: "#bf360c"; border-radius: 8 }
}

Title -> Structure
Structure -> Update
Update -> Query
Query -> Properties
Properties -> Use
